<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>No. 569
                    The Ambassador in Italy
                     (
                        Kirk
                    ) to the Acting Secretary of
                            State</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1945Berlinv01</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d569</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">569</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1945-06-24T12:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1945-06-24T12:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-06-24T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-06-24T12:00:00-05:00" n="569" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d569">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Control (<persName corresp="#p_I2">Italy</persName>) /6–2445: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 569<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in <persName corresp="#p_I2">Italy</persName>
                    </hi> (<persName corresp="#p_KMGNJ1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">us urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Caserta</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-06-24T19:00:00+02:00">June 24, 1945—7 p. m</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2749. Re our immediately preceding tel<note n="1" xml:id="d569fn1">Not
                        printed.</note> and your 607, June 22.<note n="2" xml:id="d569fn2">
                        <ref target="#d565">Document No. 565</ref>.</note> When Gen <persName corresp="#p_MLGWD1">Morgan</persName> reported to <gloss target="#t_AFHQ1">AFHQ</gloss> signature of agreement with Yugos he made no ref to exception
                    re Art. 3 and Belgrade learned of it before ourselves because <persName corresp="#p_CCJRS1">Col Clarke</persName> Brit <gloss target="#t_MilAtt1">Mil Attaché</gloss> Belgrade was present during negotiations and kept Brit
                    Ambass[ador] Belgrade<note n="3" xml:id="d569fn3">
                        <persName corresp="#p_SRCS1">R. C. Skrine Stevenson</persName>.</note> fully
                    informed. On <persName corresp="#p_MLGWD1">Morgan</persName>’s return to <gloss target="#t_AFHQ1">AFHQ</gloss> when we asked for text as set forth in our
                    2725, June 22<note n="4" xml:id="d569fn4">
                        <ref target="#d566">Document No. 566</ref>.</note> he withheld copy until he
                    could “explain” text. He did not mention reservation re Art 3 of Belgrade
                    agreement until he held meeting referred to in our 2725. Text of Yugo
                    reservation has already been sent to <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss>
                    <note n="5" xml:id="d569fn5">See <ref target="#d561">document No.
                        561</ref>.</note> …</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . .</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_KMGNJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Kirk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
</TEI>
